	<objectId>f16ca910-51c4-9096-9dd4-e8d6825eb5f6</objectId>
	<internal-name>Sec 1</internal-name>
	<sectionClass_s>no-margin-bottom</sectionClass_s>
	<file-name>f16ca910-51c4-9096-9dd4-e8d6825eb5f6.xml</file-name>
	<sectionContent_html>&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;No problem, that&amp;rsquo;s a nice small, manageable amount, right?&lt;br /&gt;Wrong!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;On a debt of R10 000 and paying only the minimum payment (let&amp;rsquo;s say 3% of the balance at 18% interest rate), it&amp;rsquo;ll take you over 17 years to pay off that debt and in the end you would&amp;rsquo;ve paid R9 500 on interest alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Treat: Paying off your credit card debt at the end of the month&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Basically, this is the best way to make your credit cards work for you without getting yourself into a debt hole and paying double your actual debt amount like we saw above. By clearing your credit card at the end of every month, you get to maximise benefits from usage rewards such as eBucks, without incurring any interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;But if you don&amp;rsquo;t have the discipline to do this, the better option is to rather save every month towards that item you want to buy.&lt;/p&gt;</sectionContent_html>
