	</item>	<item datasource="sections" inline="true">	<key>0dc2e7a9-8c2a-26e6-38de-bdd1c30adba3</key>
	<value>Sec 2</value>
<component id="0dc2e7a9-8c2a-26e6-38de-bdd1c30adba3">
	<content-type>/component/component-articlesection</content-type>
	<display-template>/templates/web/components/article-section.ftl</display-template>
	<no-template-required/>
	<merge-strategy>inherit-levels</merge-strategy>
	<objectGroupId>0dc2</objectGroupId>
	<objectId>0dc2e7a9-8c2a-26e6-38de-bdd1c30adba3</objectId>
	<file-name>0dc2e7a9-8c2a-26e6-38de-bdd1c30adba3.xml</file-name>
	<internal-name>Sec 2</internal-name>
	<sectionClass_s>no-margin-bottom</sectionClass_s>
	<sectionContent_html>&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Tax&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class="fw-900 no-margin-bottom" style="margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: var(--body-line-height); font-weight: 900; color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Trick: Believing SARS when they say that tax avoidance is the same as tax evasion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="no-margin-top" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); margin-top: 0px; color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;SARS wants you to pay as much tax as possible, and they&amp;rsquo;ll do and say anything they can to convince you that paying anything but the maximum possible tax, is somehow a problem for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Pro tip: It isn&amp;rsquo;t.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;First, let&amp;rsquo;s be clear about what the difference between tax avoidance and tax evasion is.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Tax avoidance is using tax legislation to your advantage to reduce your tax burden through lawful, legitimate means.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Tax evasion refers to using unlawful methods to avoid paying tax. We are certainly not promoting tax evasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="fw-900 no-margin-bottom" style="margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: var(--body-line-height); font-weight: 900; color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Treat: Use tax law to legally reduce your tax burden&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="no-margin-top" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); margin-top: 0px; color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;The easiest way to legally reduce your tax liability is through contributing to a retirement annuity. Contributions that you make there, within certain limits, are tax-deductible. For example: If you earn R500 000 a year, and contribute R50 000 to an RA during the year, you&amp;rsquo;re only taxed on R450 000 [There are some limits to what you are able to deduct though].&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;There are other ways as well, for example donating money to charities, working from home (in some instances) and certain investments. Your Velocity Club financial adviser will be able to give you more information about this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Emergency fund&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class="fw-900 no-margin-bottom" style="margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: var(--body-line-height); font-weight: 900; color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Trick: Using credit cards or debt to fund unexpected life expenses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="no-margin-top" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); margin-top: 0px; color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Unexpected emergencies suck. Whether its car repairs, home repairs, or medical bills, the cost is usually not small and most of us are usually unprepared for it. To get through it, we turn to credit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;The problem with this is that thanks to credit card trickery (see above), you can end up paying so much more than the amount you actually needed. And this isn&amp;rsquo;t helped by the way financial institutions eagerly offer us debt facilities.&lt;/p&gt;</sectionContent_html>
